WEBVTT

00:00.801 --> 00:02.735
[Music playing]

00:04.000 --> 00:10.074
Advertise your product or brand here
contact www.OpenSubtitles.org today

00:27.695 --> 00:29.663
GIRL: My mama told me once,

00:29.697 --> 00:33.134
"Hope is the only God
common to all men.

00:33.167 --> 00:37.138
Those who have nothing
still have hope."

00:37.171 --> 00:38.372
[train horn blows]

00:42.576 --> 00:46.414
This is Bent Arrow,
a small town in West Texas,

00:46.447 --> 00:49.417
if you still want
to call it a town.

00:49.450 --> 00:51.285
I heard it was once,

00:51.319 --> 00:52.653
before the Mega-Mart
came and left,

00:52.686 --> 00:56.557
but not since I can remember.

00:56.590 --> 01:00.228
Now it seems it's just people
passing on the highway,

01:00.261 --> 01:02.263
trains rolling through, taking
something to somewhere else

01:02.296 --> 01:04.397
and leaving a bunch of us
hanging our hats

01:04.432 --> 01:08.402
on the last hook
of a whole lot of hope.

01:40.901 --> 01:43.771
* These old highways

01:46.340 --> 01:50.211
* These old back roads

01:51.679 --> 01:55.416
* As crooked
as an arrow *

01:59.887 --> 02:02.590
* Is where I'm from

02:08.696 --> 02:10.464
* The desert

02:10.497 --> 02:12.500
* The... The dust.

02:13.934 --> 02:14.935
Ahh.

02:14.968 --> 02:16.837
[Snorts]

02:16.870 --> 02:18.472
[Nickers]

02:18.506 --> 02:20.241
What?
Is it the melody?

02:20.274 --> 02:21.575
What's not
working for you?

02:21.609 --> 02:22.543
[Neighs]

02:24.645 --> 02:26.580
[Playing guitar]

02:28.682 --> 02:31.852
* As crooked as an arrow

02:32.953 --> 02:35.389
* Is where I'm from.

02:40.394 --> 02:41.762
Big storm last night.

02:41.795 --> 02:43.831
Did it scare you?

02:43.864 --> 02:45.433
A little.

02:45.466 --> 02:46.534
You dream?

02:46.567 --> 02:48.602
A little.

02:51.239 --> 02:52.340
Ooh.

02:53.507 --> 02:54.742
How 'bout this one?

02:54.775 --> 02:55.709
You sure?

02:56.777 --> 02:58.812
Whatever you want.

02:58.846 --> 03:00.248
See you in town?

03:01.249 --> 03:02.483
In a while.

03:02.516 --> 03:04.685
I want to see
if there's a lunch rush.

03:09.257 --> 03:10.324
Bye, Joe Boy.

03:10.358 --> 03:11.659
[Neighs]

03:11.692 --> 03:13.627
[Music playing]

03:41.989 --> 03:44.758
[Radio playing
country and western music]

03:44.792 --> 03:48.462
I say Aerosmith.

03:48.496 --> 03:50.331
Nope. Springsteen.

03:50.364 --> 03:51.599
What about
Green Day?

03:51.632 --> 03:52.733
They're
an American band.

03:52.766 --> 03:54.335
They been around
for a while.

03:54.368 --> 03:55.703
Yeah. Don't they
have that guy

03:55.736 --> 03:57.838
that wore the,
uh, G.W. Bush mask
onstage?

03:57.871 --> 04:00.308
How 'bout
if we talk about
something relevant?

04:00.341 --> 04:02.810
Those punks are lucky
they didn't get
Dixie Chicked.

04:02.843 --> 04:04.878
Dixie Chicks. Now,
what happened to them?

04:04.912 --> 04:06.480
That's what
I'm talking about.

04:06.514 --> 04:07.815
You don't mess
with Texas.

04:12.353 --> 04:14.422
You know
how long ago that was?

04:14.455 --> 04:16.055
Can we
just move on here?

04:16.089 --> 04:17.725
Speaking of moving on,
you ever gonna
pay them bills,

04:17.757 --> 04:19.026
or are you gonna
make stacks out of 'em?

04:22.396 --> 04:24.432
You ever gonna pay
your damn bar tab?

04:24.465 --> 04:25.699
Hoo.
Maybe I could send you

04:25.733 --> 04:27.501
over to the vendors
to perform sexual acts,

04:27.535 --> 04:30.003
wipe out
some of the debt
that I've got here.

04:30.037 --> 04:30.971
GIRL: Ledball.
Hmm?

04:33.974 --> 04:35.343
Come on.
How about it, Merlin?

04:35.343 --> 04:37.010
Take one for the team.
Wait a sec.

04:37.044 --> 04:38.646
You might end up
owing more.

04:39.747 --> 04:40.714
That was funny.

04:40.748 --> 04:41.782
* Jack-O-Lope.

04:41.815 --> 04:42.783
Very funny.

04:42.816 --> 04:43.884
* Jack-O-Lope

04:43.917 --> 04:45.486
* Get ourself
a Jack-O-Lope *

04:52.092 --> 04:53.761
She doing
any better, darling?

04:54.862 --> 04:56.430
No, sir.

04:57.531 --> 04:58.732
All right. Well...

04:58.766 --> 05:00.067
you keep the faith.

05:01.902 --> 05:04.004
Now, you keep
that bottle hidden.

05:04.037 --> 05:06.407
Run along so we
don't have any problems.

05:06.440 --> 05:08.008
Yes, sir.

05:08.041 --> 05:09.443
Yes, ma'am.

05:09.477 --> 05:10.678
[Chuckles]

05:10.711 --> 05:12.380
Thank you, Ledball.

05:15.716 --> 05:18.719
All right,
get on out of here. Go on.

05:18.752 --> 05:23.090
* ...each other
with the grace of a love *

05:23.123 --> 05:24.858
* You just smile

05:24.892 --> 05:28.496
* And it comes back
your way... *

05:29.630 --> 05:30.964
Ledball,

05:30.998 --> 05:32.633
what'd I tell
you about that?

05:32.666 --> 05:34.702
I don't want
to see her in here.

05:34.735 --> 05:36.404
Then you
close your eyes.

05:36.437 --> 05:37.638
'Cause to me,
it looks like

05:37.671 --> 05:38.906
you're giving liquor
to a minor.

05:38.939 --> 05:40.708
And making Lois' life
a little easier,

05:40.741 --> 05:43.110
so we'll just leave it
at that, all right?

05:43.143 --> 05:47.581
* ...gets heavy
in this town *

05:47.615 --> 05:49.550
[music playing]

06:21.014 --> 06:22.450
Mama?

06:25.686 --> 06:26.754
Mama.

06:26.787 --> 06:28.088
Mama.

06:28.121 --> 06:29.623
Mama. [Kisses]

06:29.657 --> 06:30.858
[Moaning]
Come on.

06:30.891 --> 06:33.561
[Mumbling]

06:33.594 --> 06:34.995
Hi.

06:35.028 --> 06:37.097
Ah, come on. Come on.

06:37.130 --> 06:38.098
I got you. Ready?

06:38.131 --> 06:41.702
1, 2, 3.
[moaning]

06:41.735 --> 06:42.670
GIRL: Okay.

06:49.843 --> 06:52.179
How you feeling, Mama?

06:52.212 --> 06:55.816
I'm making it, baby.

06:55.849 --> 06:58.218
[Sighs]

06:58.251 --> 07:03.090
What would I do
without you, sweetie, hmm?

07:03.123 --> 07:05.926
Can I get
something for you?

07:05.959 --> 07:08.529
No, baby.

07:08.562 --> 07:11.699
The Lord is gonna
have to do the rest.

07:15.936 --> 07:21.509
I just wish that
I could be sure
that you're gonna be okay.

07:23.043 --> 07:26.079
Mm, my baby girl.

07:26.113 --> 07:27.080
[Cries softly]

07:27.114 --> 07:28.248
I know you're worried,

07:28.281 --> 07:29.917
but please
don't worry about me.

07:29.950 --> 07:30.951
Okay.
Okay?

07:30.984 --> 07:32.686
Mm-hmm.
I'm just fine.

07:32.720 --> 07:34.187
Okay.

07:34.221 --> 07:37.858
I just don't want you
to hurt no more.

07:37.891 --> 07:39.960
No.

07:39.993 --> 07:41.829
Well, you learned
all your lessons here,

07:41.862 --> 07:43.864
so you can walk
with God, right?

07:43.897 --> 07:45.999
[Chuckles]

07:46.033 --> 07:48.135
That's right, baby.

07:48.168 --> 07:49.570
[Chuckles]

07:49.603 --> 07:52.540
How was I
so blessed with you?

07:54.041 --> 07:56.176
After your sister...

07:56.209 --> 07:57.645
[coughing]

07:57.678 --> 07:59.713
Things work out
themselves, Mama.

07:59.747 --> 08:01.715
Oh, I know that, baby.

08:01.749 --> 08:03.584
[Coughs]
Mom.

08:03.617 --> 08:05.553
It just makes me so mad.

08:05.553 --> 08:06.854
Stop. Stop. Stop, okay?

08:06.887 --> 08:07.921
What?

08:07.955 --> 08:09.923
I'm right here.
Look at me,

08:09.957 --> 08:11.091
okay?

08:11.124 --> 08:12.860
Yeah.

08:12.893 --> 08:15.829
Everything's just fine,
okay?

08:15.863 --> 08:17.598
All right.

08:17.631 --> 08:19.667
Don't upset yourself.

08:19.700 --> 08:20.834
Okay.

08:20.868 --> 08:22.035
Yeah.

08:22.069 --> 08:23.671
Mama, I'm right here.

08:23.704 --> 08:25.673
I'm not leaving you.
I promise.

08:25.706 --> 08:27.240
You sure?
Oh, yes.

08:27.274 --> 08:30.243
You're my mama.

08:30.277 --> 08:32.011
You're my baby girl.

08:32.044 --> 08:33.013
Yeah.

08:33.046 --> 08:35.248
I love you.

08:35.282 --> 08:36.817
Heh.

08:36.850 --> 08:37.851
Go to sleep.

08:37.885 --> 08:40.754
Okay. Okay.

08:40.788 --> 08:42.856
Okay.
Okay.

08:45.659 --> 08:47.027
[Groans]

08:48.596 --> 08:49.863
Where's my bottle, baby?

08:51.732 --> 08:52.700
I got it.

08:52.733 --> 08:53.867
Okay.

08:59.707 --> 09:01.742
Stay with me?

09:01.775 --> 09:02.743
I'm right here.

09:02.776 --> 09:05.145
Okay.

09:05.178 --> 09:07.615
Okay.

09:07.615 --> 09:09.617
[Train rattling]

09:19.059 --> 09:21.729
You're home early.

09:21.762 --> 09:23.964
Yeah.

09:23.997 --> 09:25.633
I'm glad.

09:30.303 --> 09:32.039
Come on.
Come on, boy.

09:35.142 --> 09:37.077
[Wind chimes tinkling]

09:39.980 --> 09:41.782
Did you mail the card?

09:41.815 --> 09:43.283
Yeah.

09:44.885 --> 09:47.220
[Sighs]

09:49.156 --> 09:50.090
Cotton...

09:52.392 --> 09:55.729
things may get worse
before they get better.

09:55.763 --> 09:57.831
[Sighs]

09:57.865 --> 10:00.768
It depends
on how you look
at those things.

10:00.801 --> 10:03.971
Heh.
I suppose that's true.

10:04.004 --> 10:06.740
Do you think, Butch,

10:06.774 --> 10:08.742
that if you
believe in something...

10:08.776 --> 10:12.212
And I mean like
you just really
believe in it...

10:12.245 --> 10:14.614
That it'll come true?

10:15.849 --> 10:17.918
Well...

10:22.990 --> 10:25.125
Sure.

10:25.158 --> 10:27.661
Mama's going
to Heaven, Butch.

10:29.930 --> 10:32.666
I saw it in my dream
last night.

10:32.700 --> 10:34.301
I know she is, too.

10:45.713 --> 10:48.181
Cotton.

10:48.215 --> 10:50.317
Yeah?

10:50.350 --> 10:53.053
I'll be here.

10:54.855 --> 10:56.323
I know.

11:21.181 --> 11:23.350
[Sighs]

11:29.256 --> 11:31.825
MAN: Your mama's
in a better place.

11:31.859 --> 11:34.094
[Radio chatter
outside]

11:34.127 --> 11:35.896
[Door closes]

11:35.929 --> 11:37.931
[Overlapping chatter]

11:42.770 --> 11:44.872
Oh, God.

11:52.445 --> 11:53.380
Hey, Butch.

11:55.082 --> 11:56.917
How's she doing?

11:56.950 --> 11:58.451
She hasn't even cried yet.

11:59.820 --> 12:01.321
Kinda weird, huh?

12:03.456 --> 12:05.392
She knew this was
gonna happen.

12:09.129 --> 12:10.798
One moment?

12:38.358 --> 12:40.260
[Inhales]

13:27.007 --> 13:28.575
[Sighs]

13:46.593 --> 13:48.962
[Squawking]

13:50.230 --> 13:52.232
SHERIFF:
But you know I can't.

13:52.265 --> 13:53.600
BUTCH: But, Sheriff...

13:53.633 --> 13:54.968
Come on, Butch.

13:55.002 --> 13:57.337
Just give me a day
to figure this out.

13:57.370 --> 13:59.072
No! There's
no more talking.

13:59.106 --> 14:00.941
What are you
gonna do now?

14:00.974 --> 14:03.010
Gotta take her
to the home in Austin.

14:03.043 --> 14:04.011
Don't do that.

14:04.044 --> 14:06.279
Butch, I got no choice!

14:06.313 --> 14:10.117
Texas law,
chapter 153-002.

14:10.150 --> 14:14.187
The best interest of
the child shall be given
highest consideration.

14:14.221 --> 14:16.389
You're not
her legal guardian.

14:16.423 --> 14:18.091
Honed up on your law,
did you?

14:18.125 --> 14:20.460
Butch, I can't
just leave her here

14:20.493 --> 14:23.030
with a can of ravioli.

14:23.063 --> 14:25.632
Oh, come on now.
Just hold on a second.

14:25.665 --> 14:28.335
Come on, Butch.
This is hard enough already.

14:30.003 --> 14:32.272
I got no choice.

14:33.373 --> 14:34.374
Sunny!

14:34.407 --> 14:36.209
Oh! Oh, I knew
you'd come!

14:38.211 --> 14:39.446
Thank you.

14:39.479 --> 14:41.514
Thank you. Thank you.
Thank you. Thank you.

14:41.548 --> 14:43.216
I knew you'd come.
Cotton?

14:43.250 --> 14:44.484
Yes.

14:46.653 --> 14:48.455
Hi.
Hi.

14:48.488 --> 14:51.091
Um, what's going on?

14:51.124 --> 14:53.160
Why is
the Sheriff here?

14:54.627 --> 14:57.998
They just took
Mama to get ready
to go to Heaven.

14:59.099 --> 15:00.333
She's dead?

15:03.270 --> 15:06.239
Uh, I'm Sheriff Perez.

15:06.273 --> 15:09.142
I'm sorry
for your loss, ma'am.

15:09.176 --> 15:13.080
Lois left a copy
of her living trust
at my office

15:13.113 --> 15:15.248
when she knew
she was getting bad.

15:15.282 --> 15:19.386
It names you
as Cotton's guardian.

15:19.419 --> 15:21.088
Cotton gets the house.

15:21.121 --> 15:22.422
You get Cotton.

15:22.455 --> 15:24.291
Are you kidding me?

15:24.324 --> 15:26.994
Now you have to accept
the responsibility,

15:26.994 --> 15:28.628
or I can't leave her
with you.

15:28.661 --> 15:32.032
I just came home to...

15:32.065 --> 15:34.034
For three days
just to say goodbye.

15:34.067 --> 15:37.237
I can't take
responsibility for her.

15:37.270 --> 15:39.406
If you don't,
I'm gonna have

15:39.439 --> 15:41.241
to take her to
the children's home.

15:41.274 --> 15:45.512
Now, I have
to hear you accept
the responsibility.

15:47.414 --> 15:49.016
Sunny.

15:53.686 --> 15:55.322
I guess so.

15:56.556 --> 15:58.525
Thank you.

15:58.558 --> 16:00.293
I knew you'd say yes.

16:00.327 --> 16:01.394
Okay, come on.

16:01.428 --> 16:02.729
I want to get
your stuff inside.

16:02.762 --> 16:04.531
All right, come on.

16:09.202 --> 16:11.438
We could go inside
and...

16:15.175 --> 16:17.577
You call me if she bolts.

16:17.610 --> 16:19.379
Yeah, I'll do that.

16:20.647 --> 16:22.182
We can do our toes.

16:22.215 --> 16:23.650
Oh, then can
listen to music,

16:23.683 --> 16:25.785
and then we
can have a party.

16:25.818 --> 16:27.154
Oh. [Sighs]

16:28.755 --> 16:31.291
[Sighs]
I gotta pee.

16:31.324 --> 16:34.361
Oh, I'm in your room,
so do you want it back?

16:34.394 --> 16:35.762
Are you putting on
new lipstick?

16:35.795 --> 16:37.564
'Cause I would
love to see that,
you know.

16:37.597 --> 16:39.099
I've never
really put lipstick
on before.

16:41.468 --> 16:43.070
You need anything?

16:46.773 --> 16:48.175
Come on.

16:49.842 --> 16:52.112
[Sighs]
Damn it.

16:54.781 --> 16:55.748
[Door slides]

16:55.782 --> 16:57.217
You done peeing?

16:57.250 --> 16:58.285
How 'bout knocking?

16:58.318 --> 16:59.619
Lock's broke.

16:59.652 --> 17:01.188
Girls pee together,
right?

17:03.323 --> 17:06.159
I mean, I always see them
go to the bathroom together.

17:06.193 --> 17:08.295
I never do, though.
It's kind of gross.

17:08.328 --> 17:09.729
Maybe this was
a mistake.

17:09.762 --> 17:13.165
Why? Hasn't it
been long enough?

17:14.601 --> 17:16.203
Long enough for what?

17:16.236 --> 17:17.770
Well, it seems like
whatever made you leave,

17:17.804 --> 17:18.671
it's been long enough.

17:20.473 --> 17:25.145
So would you like
some sugar in your coffee?

17:25.178 --> 17:28.415
I could do brown sugar,
or I could do cream.

17:28.448 --> 17:32.152
I can make pancakes, too,
if you like pancakes.

17:32.185 --> 17:34.154
[Music playing]

17:41.194 --> 17:43.363
"Do not withhold good
from those who deserve it

17:43.396 --> 17:47.500
"when it is
in your power to act.

17:47.534 --> 17:51.571
"Lay hold of my words
with all your heart.

17:51.604 --> 17:55.308
Keep my commands,
and you will live..."

17:56.809 --> 18:00.213
"will get wisdom,
understanding."

18:02.149 --> 18:05.485
"Do not forget my words
or swerve from them."

18:07.554 --> 18:08.755
Amen.

18:35.448 --> 18:37.484
Fly free, my baby.

18:48.861 --> 18:51.831
How you doing, hon?

18:51.864 --> 18:53.600
Are you okay?

18:55.602 --> 19:00.907
Butch, I want you
to meet my sister,

19:00.940 --> 19:02.242
Sunny.

19:06.379 --> 19:08.215
Sorry for your loss.

19:52.392 --> 19:54.327
[Crickets chirping]

19:56.028 --> 19:58.998
I think I can feel
Mama here with us.

19:59.031 --> 20:01.534
She's happy now.

20:02.769 --> 20:04.937
How's she feel
about me being here?

20:07.039 --> 20:10.343
She said to drink
some more milk.

20:10.377 --> 20:12.612
Her answer
to everything.

20:13.746 --> 20:15.348
She didn't
really say that.

20:15.382 --> 20:17.317
I just made it up.

20:17.350 --> 20:20.853
Um, Cotton, we need
to talk about what's
gonna happen now.

20:20.887 --> 20:21.854
Slaw?
What?

20:21.888 --> 20:23.823
Pass the slaw,
please?

20:23.856 --> 20:25.224
Oh.

20:26.926 --> 20:28.895
Thank you.

20:35.635 --> 20:37.304
Um, so let's...
Things must...

20:40.407 --> 20:43.810
Things must have been
real different around here
when you were my age.

20:43.843 --> 20:45.512
They were.

20:45.545 --> 20:47.780
And that's
why you left?

20:47.814 --> 20:48.781
Well...

20:48.815 --> 20:50.917
Things have changed now.

20:51.984 --> 20:54.387
How so?

20:55.788 --> 20:57.724
Because...

20:57.757 --> 20:59.559
I'm full. Heh.

21:00.827 --> 21:02.395
[Sighs]

21:02.429 --> 21:04.697
I can't keep my eyes open.

21:07.867 --> 21:09.802
I'm glad you're here...

21:11.971 --> 21:13.506
and I love you.

21:17.377 --> 21:18.778
Night.

21:18.811 --> 21:19.746
Night.

21:22.649 --> 21:24.083
BUTCH: * Say you need me
[guitar playing]

21:24.116 --> 21:26.986
* I'll jump in the car

21:30.022 --> 21:31.991
* Drive all night

21:33.059 --> 21:35.362
* Most of the day

21:35.362 --> 21:39.832
* Just to hear
what you have to say *

21:41.501 --> 21:43.470
* Look for me

21:43.503 --> 21:45.938
* Sometime tomorrow.

21:45.972 --> 21:47.774
What a fruitcake.

21:49.976 --> 21:52.445
* Look for me

21:52.479 --> 21:55.982
* I know it's hard

21:56.015 --> 21:57.950
[truck approaching]

22:01.053 --> 22:06.426
* Look for me
coming down your... *

22:06.459 --> 22:08.395
Shit.

22:12.999 --> 22:14.534
No way!

22:14.567 --> 22:17.770
Can't be!
Sunny?

22:17.804 --> 22:18.771
Sunny Thompson?

22:18.805 --> 22:20.573
Hey, Jackson.

22:20.607 --> 22:22.742
'Cause the Sunny I know,
she's in Hollywood.

22:22.775 --> 22:24.010
I saw her on cable
the other night.

22:24.043 --> 22:26.679
What was the name
you used?

22:26.713 --> 22:28.014
Sunny Morning.

22:28.047 --> 22:29.516
Sunny Morning.
That's it.

22:29.549 --> 22:31.584
It's a good one,
too, yeah.

22:31.618 --> 22:33.720
I mean,
what's a big-time
Hollywood actress

22:33.753 --> 22:35.555
doing on back here
in Bent Arrow, huh?

22:35.588 --> 22:37.824
We buried Lois today.

22:37.857 --> 22:41.561
Right. Wow.
[chuckles]

22:41.594 --> 22:44.764
Uh, Tammy,
come on over here.

22:44.797 --> 22:46.599
Meet Sunny.
This is Sunny Thompson.

22:46.633 --> 22:49.836
Hmm. She's not
as pretty in person.

22:49.869 --> 22:51.771
She's sweet.

22:51.804 --> 22:53.640
Aw, come on.

22:53.673 --> 22:56.509
You didn't think
I was gonna wait around
for you, did you?

22:56.543 --> 22:58.678
I'm the one
that left, remember?

22:58.711 --> 23:00.880
Yeah, I do remember that.

23:03.483 --> 23:05.618
It's getting late,
old boy.

23:05.652 --> 23:06.719
See you later.

23:13.092 --> 23:14.727
Still drinking
and driving, huh?

23:14.761 --> 23:16.796
Got it down now.

23:16.829 --> 23:18.598
Good for you.

23:18.631 --> 23:20.567
Come on, baby.
Let's go.

23:20.600 --> 23:22.769
Go wait in the car.

23:24.236 --> 23:25.171
[Scoffs]

23:33.946 --> 23:36.883
What say I, uh,
drop Tammy home, come back?

23:36.916 --> 23:38.918
We can have
a couple of drinks,

23:38.951 --> 23:40.487
maybe catch up and talk.

23:40.520 --> 23:41.988
What do you think?

23:42.021 --> 23:43.590
I don't think so.

23:43.623 --> 23:45.091
Why not?

23:45.124 --> 23:47.994
'Cause I think we've
been down that road,

23:48.027 --> 23:49.996
and we done
wore its ass out.

23:50.029 --> 23:53.032
Still think you're too good
for the rest of us, don't you?

23:53.065 --> 23:57.003
That's not what I said.

23:57.036 --> 23:58.004
[Slams hood]

23:58.037 --> 23:59.238
David Jackson,
you said hi!

23:59.271 --> 24:00.907
Now get in the car!

24:00.940 --> 24:03.209
She's a keeper.
You should hold on
to her.

24:03.242 --> 24:05.144
You know, you and I,

24:05.177 --> 24:08.214
we could have had
a couple of kids by now,

24:08.247 --> 24:09.949
could have had a future.

24:09.982 --> 24:13.553
Instead, all you got's
a crappy past.

25:34.967 --> 25:36.268
* Still

25:39.205 --> 25:41.207
* Falling

25:46.012 --> 25:50.617
* Breathless and all

25:50.617 --> 25:52.151
* Begin

25:57.089 --> 25:59.191
* Inside

26:01.828 --> 26:03.630
* Today

26:08.735 --> 26:12.171
* Beside me

26:13.305 --> 26:15.207
* Today

26:19.211 --> 26:20.647
* Around...

26:20.647 --> 26:22.114
LOIS: What are you
doing with my suitcase?

26:22.148 --> 26:23.349
What is that?

26:23.382 --> 26:25.918
What do you mean,
taking it with you?

26:25.952 --> 26:27.987
Getting out of here?
Are you crazy?

26:28.020 --> 26:30.256
You know where
your fight is, honey.

26:30.289 --> 26:31.390
Right there.

26:31.423 --> 26:33.660
You run
as far as you want.

26:33.693 --> 26:36.663
It's gonna be right here
when you get back.

26:36.696 --> 26:37.930
L.A.?

26:37.964 --> 26:40.399
You won't last
for two seconds in L.A.

26:40.432 --> 26:44.804
God, it's ridiculous,
totally ridiculous.

26:47.039 --> 26:48.675
[Frame shatters]

27:03.455 --> 27:06.425
MERLIN: The secret
remedy for a headache,
you know what it is?

27:06.458 --> 27:07.694
Uh, let's see.
Next up.

27:07.727 --> 27:08.995
Some kind
of a meat product?

27:09.028 --> 27:10.797
You want to know
the answer?

27:10.830 --> 27:12.331
Um...
Foot massage.

27:12.364 --> 27:14.133
You get a foot massage,

27:14.166 --> 27:16.168
take care of any headache
you got.

27:16.202 --> 27:17.269
Also if you get 'em...

27:17.303 --> 27:19.706
I want you to watch
your language.

27:19.739 --> 27:22.041
Why? You got
a headache?

27:22.074 --> 27:24.210
Hi.

27:24.243 --> 27:25.978
You were at the funeral,
weren't you?

27:26.012 --> 27:27.880
Yes, ma'am.

27:27.914 --> 27:29.782
I guess you
don't remember me.

27:29.816 --> 27:30.917
My name's Ledball.

27:30.950 --> 27:33.119
I was a friend
of your mother's.

27:33.152 --> 27:34.854
I'm so sorry
for your loss,

27:34.887 --> 27:36.322
but it's good
to have you back.

27:36.355 --> 27:37.790
Thank you.

27:39.291 --> 27:42.261
Uh, could I get
you something?

27:42.294 --> 27:43.262
A beer, maybe?

27:43.295 --> 27:46.465
No. Um, I was wondering

27:46.498 --> 27:48.000
if... if you were hiring.

27:48.034 --> 27:49.201
[laughter]

27:53.272 --> 27:56.008
I'm sorry, ma'am.
They don't mean nothing.

27:56.042 --> 27:58.210
Just things have been
mighty slow around here.

27:58.244 --> 27:59.311
Mighty slow.
Oh, goodness.

27:59.345 --> 28:00.312
It's all right.

28:00.346 --> 28:01.413
[laughter]

28:01.447 --> 28:03.750
I wish I could, Sunny.
I really do.

28:06.352 --> 28:08.220
Sorry about Lois.

28:08.254 --> 28:09.355
We all loved her.

28:09.388 --> 28:12.024
Yeah. It's
a damn shame.

28:14.293 --> 28:16.295
Yeah.

28:16.328 --> 28:18.197
Are you hungry,
honey?

28:20.232 --> 28:22.401
Yeah, I'm... I am.

28:22.434 --> 28:24.303
Um, can I get

28:24.336 --> 28:26.773
a grilled cheese
and a Coke to go?

28:26.773 --> 28:27.974
Yes, ma'am. Coming up.

28:29.876 --> 28:32.111
No, you put
that money away.

28:32.144 --> 28:34.480
Your money's
not good here.

28:34.513 --> 28:36.783
I can do this much
at least.

28:36.783 --> 28:38.250
Oh, thank you.
[soda spritzes]

28:38.284 --> 28:40.887
You know,

28:40.920 --> 28:44.223
your Mama and I go back
to the third grade.

28:44.256 --> 28:47.794
She used
to chase me around
and try to kiss me.

28:47.827 --> 28:48.995
[Chuckles]

28:49.028 --> 28:51.430
By the ninth grade,
I let her catch me.

28:51.463 --> 28:54.834
That must have been
a spit-drenched fiasco.

28:54.867 --> 28:56.969
[laughs]

28:57.003 --> 28:58.905
You still wearing
women's panties?

28:58.938 --> 29:00.339
I have
a medical condition.

29:00.372 --> 29:02.441
It's the doctor's orders.
I have a medica...

29:02.474 --> 29:03.542
I have a prescription.
[laughter]

29:03.575 --> 29:04.811
Doctor's condition?

29:04.811 --> 29:06.278
It's a prescription.

29:06.312 --> 29:07.279
Doctor's...

29:07.313 --> 29:09.348
I have a rash.
Sure, it is.

29:09.381 --> 29:10.817
I just can't...
I'll be right back

29:10.850 --> 29:12.518
with that
grilled cheese.

29:14.453 --> 29:16.422
Not like
I have emphysema.

29:16.455 --> 29:18.057
I have a rash.

29:20.359 --> 29:21.360
Hmm.

29:21.393 --> 29:23.830
Oh, God!
I can't believe...

29:23.830 --> 29:25.832
21! That makes
five whole dollars!

29:25.832 --> 29:27.066
Winner, winner,
chicken dinner.

29:27.099 --> 29:28.367
You're buying me
chicken dinner.

29:28.400 --> 29:29.902
Your choice.
[both laugh]

29:31.037 --> 29:32.204
Hey, all.

29:32.238 --> 29:34.240
Sunny.

29:35.341 --> 29:37.844
So it's you.

29:37.877 --> 29:39.478
Guilty.

29:39.511 --> 29:41.080
You don't look like
the type of person

29:41.113 --> 29:42.348
that would
sit around
and paint postcards.

29:42.381 --> 29:45.017
Yeah? What does someone
like that look like?

29:46.418 --> 29:47.887
Not you.

29:47.920 --> 29:49.021
Sunny.

29:49.055 --> 29:51.223
Would it help
if I chop my ear off?

30:03.202 --> 30:06.973
Well, get a load
of this retail giant.

30:07.006 --> 30:09.008
Hi, Mr. Morgan.

30:09.041 --> 30:10.576
Bobby?

30:12.044 --> 30:13.913
[Sighs]

30:13.946 --> 30:17.616
Oh, you know you'd
be doing me a big
personal favor, Butchie,

30:17.649 --> 30:20.219
if you would, uh,
take this rattrap down.

30:20.252 --> 30:22.354
You have any idea
how much money

30:22.388 --> 30:25.024
I'm spending trying
to bring this town
back to where it was?

30:25.057 --> 30:26.025
Not a clue.

30:26.058 --> 30:27.626
Well, it's a lot.

30:27.659 --> 30:29.628
And it's things
just like this

30:29.661 --> 30:33.199
that just keep this town
drying out day after day.

30:34.333 --> 30:35.902
The Lord
mocks proud mockers,

30:35.935 --> 30:38.270
but gives grace
to the humble,
Mr. Morgan.

30:38.304 --> 30:42.108
Well, aren't you
the precocious little critter?

30:47.113 --> 30:51.183
What are you doing
hanging out with this
washed-up has-been?

30:51.217 --> 30:53.085
Hi, Mr. Morgan.

30:56.322 --> 30:59.491
Well, Jackson told me
that you was come back.

31:00.993 --> 31:02.929
Sorry about
what happened to Lois.

31:02.962 --> 31:04.563
[Sighs]

31:04.596 --> 31:07.233
Take her down, Butch.
It's an eyesore.

31:07.266 --> 31:10.102
No... No permit.
No little lemonade stand.

31:10.136 --> 31:11.603
Do it.

31:20.479 --> 31:22.414
Wow.

31:22.448 --> 31:24.583
He hasn't
changed a bit.

31:28.420 --> 31:31.057
He's all talk.

31:34.293 --> 31:35.962
I have an idea.

31:35.995 --> 31:39.298
You up
for an adventure?

31:55.681 --> 31:59.085
Oh, my God, I haven't
been here in forever.

32:00.519 --> 32:02.188
A pool?
Ho ho ho.

32:02.221 --> 32:04.356
Look at this.
Are you kidding me?

32:04.390 --> 32:05.457
Oh, my God.

32:07.059 --> 32:08.194
Oh, wow.

32:08.227 --> 32:11.430
How'd I not know
about this place?

32:11.463 --> 32:14.533
Think we've been
hanging out with
the wrong people.

32:14.566 --> 32:17.169
1, 2, 3!

32:17.203 --> 32:18.470
BUTCH: Be careful.
[shrieks]

32:23.275 --> 32:25.411
How's the water?

32:25.444 --> 32:27.213
Perfect.

32:27.246 --> 32:29.015
Oh, yeah?

32:29.015 --> 32:30.549
What do you think?

32:30.582 --> 32:32.218
I think I'm gonna
splash you back.

32:32.251 --> 32:33.319
That's what I think.

32:33.352 --> 32:35.254
[Squeals]

32:39.391 --> 32:41.027
Mmm.

32:43.195 --> 32:44.763
I used to...

32:44.796 --> 32:48.134
I used to come up here
with... with Jackson

32:48.167 --> 32:50.136
after his dad
had these parties,

32:50.169 --> 32:52.704
and we'd steal
all of his liquor

32:52.738 --> 32:56.308
and just get wasted.

32:56.342 --> 32:57.543
[Chuckles]

32:57.576 --> 32:58.610
Sounds fun.

32:58.644 --> 33:00.412
It was fun.

33:05.317 --> 33:09.255
I would talk about
how I was gonna
take over the world

33:09.288 --> 33:12.458
and kick ass,
take names, you know,

33:12.491 --> 33:14.460
stupid stuff.

33:17.463 --> 33:19.765
It's not stupid
to dream.

33:19.798 --> 33:20.766
Well...

33:24.836 --> 33:27.139
You know,
I think everyone

33:27.173 --> 33:31.077
used to have a place
something like this.

33:31.077 --> 33:32.511
You have one?

33:34.080 --> 33:36.648
Anywhere I could score
a six-pack, park my car

33:36.682 --> 33:39.318
and find a good song
on the radio.

33:40.819 --> 33:42.788
Are you guys
gonna keep talking,

33:42.821 --> 33:44.356
or you coming in?

33:44.390 --> 33:45.724
[Squeals]

33:45.757 --> 33:48.094
[Cotton laughs]

33:48.094 --> 33:48.827
Oh, no!

33:51.763 --> 33:54.433
What are you doing?
No, no, no! Oh!

33:55.534 --> 33:57.569
[Squeals]

33:57.603 --> 33:59.571
All right, that's it!

33:59.605 --> 34:01.673
You, you...

34:01.707 --> 34:04.143
[shrieks]

34:04.176 --> 34:05.644
Well,
that could actually...

34:05.677 --> 34:06.678
Ballast?

34:06.712 --> 34:08.480
Perez!
Ballast?

34:08.514 --> 34:11.150
You keep hanging out
with these warts
on a donkey's dick,

34:11.183 --> 34:13.585
I'm gonna have to have
the county dock your wages.

34:13.619 --> 34:14.719
It's my lunch hour,
Mr. Morgan.

34:14.753 --> 34:16.222
There something
I can do for you?

34:16.255 --> 34:18.556
Yeah.
Serve an eviction notice.

34:18.590 --> 34:19.858
To who?

34:19.891 --> 34:22.261
You're four months
behind, Ledball.

34:22.293 --> 34:23.462
I heard.

34:23.495 --> 34:26.297
[Spits]
Several times now.

34:26.331 --> 34:28.467
So what are you gonna do?

34:28.500 --> 34:30.668
Rob my bank?
That should be
easy enough.

34:30.702 --> 34:32.737
You know where
the Sheriff is
all the time.

34:32.771 --> 34:35.141
I get an hour,
Mr. Morgan.

34:35.141 --> 34:36.574
I can eat
where I choose.

34:36.608 --> 34:39.210
You know,
I got some ideas
for this property.

34:39.245 --> 34:41.280
You know,
beef's making a comeback.

34:41.313 --> 34:43.282
I might just turn it
into a meatpacking plant.

34:43.315 --> 34:45.851
I could even
give you jag-offs
a job killing cattle.

34:45.884 --> 34:48.554
Heh. That means
you're gonna have
to get off your asses,

34:48.587 --> 34:51.157
and I don't think
you're capable of that.

34:51.190 --> 34:53.824
Aw, come on. Somebody's
got to do something
about this little town.

34:53.859 --> 34:56.262
It's gonna end up nothing
but spit in the footnotes.

34:56.295 --> 34:59.631
Y'all sit around here
wallowing in the past,

34:59.665 --> 35:02.868
and blinds you
to the future.

35:02.901 --> 35:06.605
Well, unlike you boys,
I've got things to do,

35:06.638 --> 35:09.441
so I will bid
you gentlemen adios,

35:09.475 --> 35:12.744
and I do use the term
"gentlemen" loosely.

35:15.214 --> 35:17.516
All right, I can't be
killing anything.

35:17.549 --> 35:19.718
I've been studying
the Buddhist culture,

35:19.751 --> 35:22.688
and I've taken me
a vow of passivism.

35:22.721 --> 35:26.492
Should have taken
a vow of silence.

35:26.525 --> 35:30.329
I'll do what I can
to slow down the process.

35:30.362 --> 35:33.699
There anything you can do
to pick things up?

35:33.732 --> 35:35.934
Not yet.

35:35.967 --> 35:39.238
I have an idea.
How 'bout a happy hour?

35:39.271 --> 35:42.708
And since when
hasn't it been
happy hour for you?

35:42.741 --> 35:45.777
Well, you know,
just a suggestion.

35:45.811 --> 35:47.813
Oh, you gotta shut up,
Cricket.

35:47.846 --> 35:49.381
It's imperative.

35:51.850 --> 35:54.253
* So sad

35:54.286 --> 35:58.524
* To be alone

35:58.557 --> 36:04.896
* Help me make it
through the night *

36:06.932 --> 36:08.700
Nice.

36:08.734 --> 36:09.968
Did you
ever try singing

36:10.001 --> 36:11.837
while you were doing
the acting thing?

36:11.870 --> 36:14.940
Oh, not really.

36:14.973 --> 36:16.642
Hmm.

36:16.675 --> 36:18.377
That's too bad.

36:20.379 --> 36:21.913
How'd you know
about the acting thing?

36:21.947 --> 36:24.683
Ah, the walls are thin,
and Jackson is loud.

36:29.321 --> 36:32.258
Cotton, we gotta go.

36:32.258 --> 36:33.259
What?

36:33.292 --> 36:34.526
We have to go.

36:34.560 --> 36:35.794
Do we have to?

36:35.827 --> 36:37.496
Yeah.
Come on. Get out.

36:39.898 --> 36:41.400
I'm hungry.

36:41.433 --> 36:43.369
Well, listen.

36:43.402 --> 36:44.736
I'm barbecuing
tonight,

36:44.770 --> 36:47.539
so, um,
if y'all would
like to come over,

36:47.573 --> 36:48.740
you know,
you're more
than welcome.

36:48.774 --> 36:49.808
Yeah.

36:49.841 --> 36:50.809
Can we, Sunny?

36:50.842 --> 36:51.810
Maybe.

36:51.843 --> 36:53.279
Oh, what am I saying?

36:53.312 --> 36:55.347
I'm not your mom.
Do what you want.

36:59.751 --> 37:00.986
I'm sorry. Come on.

37:01.019 --> 37:02.654
Grab your boots.
We'll go.

37:20.939 --> 37:22.774
Are you mad at me?

37:22.808 --> 37:24.042
What do you mean?

37:24.075 --> 37:26.912
You seemed mad when
I got out of the pool.

37:26.945 --> 37:28.514
[Sighs] No.

37:28.547 --> 37:32.318
I... I was mad at myself.

37:32.318 --> 37:33.919
Why?

37:33.952 --> 37:36.455
It's hard to explain.

37:38.724 --> 37:40.626
You like Butch,
don't you?

37:40.659 --> 37:42.894
Well, h-he's different,

37:42.928 --> 37:44.863
that's for sure.

37:44.896 --> 37:46.598
I think you like him.

37:46.632 --> 37:47.833
I didn't say that!

37:47.866 --> 37:49.801
Don't tell him
I said that.

37:49.835 --> 37:51.036
Why not?

37:51.069 --> 37:53.872
It's already
complicated enough.

37:53.905 --> 37:56.875
Does that mean
it's too hard
to explain, too?

37:56.908 --> 37:58.009
Definitely.

37:58.043 --> 37:59.945
Yeah.

37:59.978 --> 38:01.347
You know,
for a grown-up,

38:01.347 --> 38:02.781
you sure
can't explain much.

38:02.814 --> 38:04.983
You got that right.

38:09.821 --> 38:12.791
You know, Cotton,
I'm, um...

38:12.824 --> 38:15.927
I'm sorry about
what I said at the pool

38:15.961 --> 38:19.365
about not being your mother
and everything.

38:19.365 --> 38:20.566
It wasn't
very thoughtful.

38:22.133 --> 38:24.670
It's okay.

38:24.703 --> 38:26.872
I know you
didn't mean it.

38:30.609 --> 38:32.378
Looks pretty.

38:32.378 --> 38:34.079
Thanks.

38:34.112 --> 38:36.382
[Wind chimes tinkling]

38:39.785 --> 38:42.954
Cotton,
you have a bedtime?

38:42.988 --> 38:45.090
Uh-uh.

38:45.123 --> 38:48.059
But I'll go if you
sing me a lullaby.

38:50.662 --> 38:52.398
Please.

38:52.398 --> 38:53.399
[Sighs]

38:53.399 --> 38:54.400
Okay.

38:54.400 --> 38:55.801
Come here.

38:59.871 --> 39:01.540
Oh, shh.

39:04.576 --> 39:09.080
* Maybe I'll catch
that shooting star *

39:09.114 --> 39:13.819
* Just like
a firefly in a jar *

39:13.852 --> 39:16.422
* Close your eyes

39:16.422 --> 39:21.727
* Your dreams are
not that far away *

39:23.529 --> 39:25.831
Mommy used
to sing that me.

39:25.864 --> 39:27.566
Did she sing
to you, too?

39:27.599 --> 39:29.435
Mm-hmm.

39:29.468 --> 39:34.440
[Together]
* Maybe I'll meet
that cow on the moon *

39:34.440 --> 39:38.444
* Up in the clouds
there singing a tune *

39:38.477 --> 39:41.447
* The rest of the world
can sleep *

39:41.480 --> 39:43.515
* But, darling, you

39:43.549 --> 39:44.683
[laughs]

39:44.716 --> 39:48.754
* Were meant to dream.

39:56.027 --> 39:58.196
You okay?

39:58.229 --> 40:01.166
I got allergies.

40:01.199 --> 40:03.635
Come on.
I'll tuck you in bed.

40:03.669 --> 40:05.671
No. It's okay.

40:05.704 --> 40:08.540
I can
tuck myself in.

40:08.574 --> 40:09.675
Sure.

40:09.708 --> 40:10.642
Yeah. Night.

40:15.581 --> 40:16.915
Good night, honey.

40:22.187 --> 40:23.855
She blows me away.

40:25.624 --> 40:27.993
I had no idea.

40:34.700 --> 40:38.103
You have no idea how happy
she is that you're here.

40:43.041 --> 40:44.843
Can I ask you
a question?

40:44.876 --> 40:45.811
Sure.

40:48.514 --> 40:51.650
What did Morgan mean
by a washed-up has-been?

40:53.552 --> 40:56.221
I used to play
some football.

40:56.254 --> 40:57.923
Why'd you quit?

41:01.893 --> 41:03.729
This what you wanted?

41:03.762 --> 41:04.730
[Chuckles]

41:04.763 --> 41:05.897
This is what I needed.

41:09.067 --> 41:10.936
So what are you doing
for the Fourth?

41:10.969 --> 41:12.538
Oh, I don't know.

41:13.539 --> 41:14.840
Well, Joe Boy and I

41:14.873 --> 41:16.708
would consider it
a real honor

41:16.742 --> 41:20.211
if you'd like to join us
for the Fourth of July picnic.

41:20.245 --> 41:22.080
Um...

41:22.113 --> 41:24.950
if I'm still here,
I'll think about it.

41:24.983 --> 41:26.785
Still here?

41:26.818 --> 41:28.019
[Sighs]

41:28.053 --> 41:29.287
We'll see.

41:29.320 --> 41:30.656
Okay.

41:33.124 --> 41:34.192
Thanks for tonight.

41:34.225 --> 41:36.795
Sure. Anytime.

41:39.931 --> 41:40.866
Good night.

41:51.943 --> 41:55.647
You know, you could brush
your teeth once in a while.

41:55.681 --> 41:56.815
What?

41:56.848 --> 41:58.884
Ah, you don't
have to tell me.

41:58.917 --> 42:01.219
She doesn't know
if she's coming or going.

42:01.252 --> 42:02.754
And what does that say?

42:02.788 --> 42:05.323
[Snorts]

42:05.356 --> 42:07.793
I'm telling you
straight up.

42:07.826 --> 42:09.628
This one is dangerous.

42:09.661 --> 42:11.262
[Snorts]

42:11.296 --> 42:13.732
Yeah, yeah, yeah,
you're probably right.

42:13.765 --> 42:16.101
She'll do
the right thing, but...

42:16.134 --> 42:17.769
[snorts]

42:17.803 --> 42:21.306
All right, well, as long
as you're with me on this.

42:21.339 --> 42:24.209
Are you with me on this?

42:24.242 --> 42:27.278
I'm gonna take you
to the dentist.

42:31.917 --> 42:34.285
Early bird
getting the worm, huh?

42:34.319 --> 42:36.922
I just wanted to talk
to you before things
got set in your mind.

42:36.955 --> 42:38.323
About what?

42:38.356 --> 42:39.858
Sunny.

42:39.891 --> 42:40.859
What about her?

42:40.892 --> 42:42.260
You like her, don't you?

42:42.293 --> 42:44.329
Yeah, sure.

42:44.362 --> 42:46.131
I saw the way
you were looking at her

42:46.164 --> 42:47.633
at the pool
when she was singing.

42:47.633 --> 42:49.034
Well, she's a good singer.

42:49.067 --> 42:51.637
Oh, don't you lie to me.

42:51.637 --> 42:53.872
You like her,
and she likes you.

42:53.905 --> 42:55.974
Did she say that?

42:56.007 --> 42:57.909
No, but I know.

42:57.943 --> 42:58.977
Do you?

42:59.010 --> 43:01.012
Well, first off,

43:01.046 --> 43:02.914
I think y'all should
just tell each other

43:02.948 --> 43:04.215
instead of playing
those stupid games.

43:04.249 --> 43:06.752
Well, maybe we will
if we figure out we do.

43:06.785 --> 43:09.087
All I know is
Heather in my class

43:09.120 --> 43:10.756
liked this
boy named Connor,

43:10.789 --> 43:12.057
and she used
to whisper and giggle

43:12.090 --> 43:13.759
and do stupid stuff
with her friends,

43:13.792 --> 43:16.394
and he used to ignore her,

43:16.427 --> 43:18.664
and they never spoke
to each other.

43:18.697 --> 43:21.099
Well, what happened
to Heather and Connor?

43:22.868 --> 43:24.035
Connor moved.

43:24.069 --> 43:25.937
Tragedy
in the fourth grade.

43:25.971 --> 43:26.938
Yes.

43:26.972 --> 43:28.106
[Chuckles]

43:28.139 --> 43:30.776
I tell people
straight out how I feel.

43:30.809 --> 43:31.743
[Siren bloops]

43:33.178 --> 43:34.880
I know you do.

43:38.383 --> 43:41.152
Hi, Butch.
How's it going?

43:42.954 --> 43:43.955
It's going.

43:43.989 --> 43:47.358
Butch, I got a problem.

43:47.392 --> 43:50.696
Morgan's making me move
your postcard stand.

43:50.729 --> 43:53.965
Yeah, he came by here
the other day and
threw a hissy fit.

43:53.999 --> 43:58.336
Yeah. You're gonna
have to move it outside
of city limits.

43:58.369 --> 44:00.872
There's isn't
any traffic out there.

44:00.906 --> 44:04.042
Well, Butch,
there's no traffic
anywhere around here.

44:04.075 --> 44:06.044
BUTCH: Yeah,
you got a point.

44:06.077 --> 44:08.880
Shoot, I don't know
why you sit out here

44:08.914 --> 44:11.249
in the wind and
the sun for, anyway.

44:11.282 --> 44:14.352
You know,
people think you're crazy.

44:14.385 --> 44:16.387
I got my reasons.

44:16.421 --> 44:18.256
Well, they must be
some good ones.

44:18.289 --> 44:19.958
Morgan's a bully.

44:19.991 --> 44:21.727
Yeah, Morgan's a bully.

44:21.760 --> 44:23.795
Sorry, Butch.

44:24.996 --> 44:26.197
It's not your problem.

44:35.440 --> 44:37.108
Well, that sucks.

44:37.142 --> 44:39.110
Yeah, don't it?

44:39.144 --> 44:43.782
[Joe Boy neighs]

44:43.815 --> 44:46.785
Well, we both
see bright things
in your future.

44:46.818 --> 44:48.453
Oh, yeah?
What do you see?

44:48.486 --> 44:51.289
I'm not telling you.

44:51.322 --> 44:52.357
See you later.

44:52.390 --> 44:53.925
I gotta go.

44:53.959 --> 44:55.260
Where you going?

45:04.169 --> 45:06.004
What just happened?

45:07.472 --> 45:10.341
CRICKET: How much
you reckon is up there?

45:10.375 --> 45:11.943
Oh, I don't know.

45:11.977 --> 45:13.344
Maybe a grand or two.

45:13.378 --> 45:15.046
That ain't
gonna be enough.

45:15.080 --> 45:16.381
No. Really?

45:16.414 --> 45:18.049
So what's the point?

45:18.083 --> 45:19.985
Yeah, what's
the point, Ledball?

45:20.018 --> 45:22.187
You're just getting
dust in my beer.

45:22.220 --> 45:25.791
How much you reckon
I'd get for a dollar bill
signed by Janis Joplin?

45:25.791 --> 45:29.227
Whoa. You got a bill
signed by Janis Joplin?

45:29.260 --> 45:31.797
Well, one night,
she and I

45:31.830 --> 45:33.498
were running
around here in our
birthday suits,

45:33.531 --> 45:35.066
and she stuck it
up here.

45:35.100 --> 45:37.235
There was
a lot of Southern
Comfort involved,

45:37.268 --> 45:40.071
so I'm
not sure of exactly
where she put it.

45:40.105 --> 45:44.375
Lord, that's
near 40 years ago.

45:44.409 --> 45:47.112
Are you saying
that you and her...

45:49.147 --> 45:51.950
Eww.

45:51.983 --> 45:53.384
I ain't saying
nothing about no one,

45:53.418 --> 45:54.820
especially to you.

45:54.853 --> 45:57.022
Well, if it was
so damn important to you,

45:57.055 --> 45:58.489
why'd you
leave it up there?

45:58.523 --> 45:59.958
'Cause that's the deal.

45:59.991 --> 46:01.827
Well, it's stupid.
What's stupid?

46:01.860 --> 46:05.496
Ledball's looking
for a dollar bill
signed by Janis Joplin.

46:05.530 --> 46:07.198
Well, why is
that stupid?

46:07.232 --> 46:09.300
Well, because he's late
on his lease,

46:09.334 --> 46:12.237
and Morgan wants
to make us a bunch
of meatpackers.

46:13.504 --> 46:14.840
[Chuckles]

46:14.873 --> 46:15.907
Cricket,

46:15.941 --> 46:18.176
next time
you have a brain fart,

46:18.209 --> 46:19.444
seriously think
to yourself,

46:19.477 --> 46:22.047
"Do I really want
to say that?"

46:22.080 --> 46:25.150
And if you decide you do,
shut up anyway.

46:25.183 --> 46:27.853
Yeah,
he shut me down, too.

46:27.886 --> 46:30.221
Ah, bastard.

46:30.255 --> 46:31.890
What are you
gonna do?

46:33.324 --> 46:35.293
Well, I was
thinking about
setting up in here,

46:35.326 --> 46:37.362
but obviously that
ain't gonna work either.

46:37.395 --> 46:40.131
Paradise fading
by the dashboard
light.

46:40.165 --> 46:41.132
Who said that?

46:41.166 --> 46:42.400
How 'bout who cares?

46:42.433 --> 46:44.469
Nope. Wrong.

46:44.502 --> 46:47.172
Well, bitching ain't
gonna get the potato peeled
one way or the other.

46:47.205 --> 46:50.475
Yeah, but if this town
is truly gonna flourish,

46:50.508 --> 46:51.910
then we have to criticize,

46:51.943 --> 46:54.345
and if it's gonna
function as a whole,

46:54.379 --> 46:56.547
then we
have to have dissent.

46:56.581 --> 46:59.050
You want me
to cut you off?

46:59.084 --> 47:01.019
I'm just saying.

47:03.021 --> 47:04.923
Oh, my.

47:04.956 --> 47:06.424
[laughs]

47:06.457 --> 47:10.228
And here it is.

47:10.261 --> 47:12.263
What are you gonna
do with that now?

47:12.297 --> 47:14.966
I don't know.
I thought I'd
put it on eBay.

47:15.000 --> 47:16.902
There must be
some rich old boy

47:16.935 --> 47:18.436
who was
a Joplin fan.

47:18.469 --> 47:22.507
Keep Morgan
off my back
for a while.

47:22.540 --> 47:23.942
Sounds like a plan.

47:23.975 --> 47:24.943
Theoretically, yeah.

47:24.976 --> 47:27.445
Realistically,
probably not.

47:27.478 --> 47:30.982
And that's it.
You're done.

47:49.267 --> 47:50.501
Can I help you?

47:50.535 --> 47:52.603
Oh, hi.
I'm looking for Jackson.

47:52.637 --> 47:53.939
Sunny.

47:53.972 --> 47:56.474
Hey, Jackson.

47:56.507 --> 47:59.044
You didn't have
to come all this
way to see me.

47:59.077 --> 48:00.578
I know you
ain't got a car.

48:00.611 --> 48:02.513
You could have
just called.

48:02.547 --> 48:04.950
There's a bar
around the corner.

48:04.950 --> 48:07.352
Um, that's
not why I'm here.

48:07.385 --> 48:10.121
[Cellphone rings]
No? Why are you here?

48:11.656 --> 48:13.524
I need a job.

48:13.558 --> 48:15.560
Excuse me?

48:15.593 --> 48:17.595
I need a job.

48:17.628 --> 48:20.231
Seems like money
puts food on the table.

48:20.265 --> 48:22.300
After everything that's
gone down between us,

48:22.333 --> 48:23.668
that's what
you're here for?

48:23.701 --> 48:25.136
Oh, this was a mistake.

48:25.170 --> 48:26.204
No, wait.

48:29.007 --> 48:32.310
[Sighs]

48:32.343 --> 48:35.646
Well, we don't need
any more salesmen or
assistants, and...

48:35.680 --> 48:39.417
I don't suppose you
know your way around
an engine, do you?

48:39.450 --> 48:40.718
No.

48:40.751 --> 48:42.687
Guess that
leaves janitor

48:42.720 --> 48:45.456
unless your hands
are too precious
for a mop.

48:45.490 --> 48:49.127
Nope. It's kind of
what I expected.

48:49.160 --> 48:50.996
Bucket's in the back.

48:56.201 --> 48:57.702
Who's that?

48:57.735 --> 48:59.370
Nobody.

48:59.404 --> 49:01.172
Uh-huh.

49:01.206 --> 49:03.374
Is nobody
working here now?

49:03.408 --> 49:04.609
Yep.

49:04.642 --> 49:06.477
Tammy ain't
gonna like that.

49:06.511 --> 49:08.646
Tammy can
kiss my ass.

49:08.679 --> 49:12.417
* My head before

49:12.450 --> 49:17.588
* My heart gives up

49:17.622 --> 49:20.725
* Oh, better days

49:20.758 --> 49:25.530
* I've had enough

49:25.563 --> 49:27.498
* I'd turn it off

49:27.532 --> 49:32.103
* If only I knew how to

49:32.137 --> 49:38.076
* My hands are sealed
around the love I hold to *

49:40.645 --> 49:47.252
* Time will move on

49:47.285 --> 49:50.455
* Always early

49:50.488 --> 49:54.759
* Always late

49:54.792 --> 50:02.800
* I can't believe
the words you say *

50:02.833 --> 50:09.340
* They ring like stones
thrown into a canyon *

50:09.374 --> 50:15.446
* I feel the weight
of each one slowly landing *

50:18.149 --> 50:23.821
* Time will move on

50:23.854 --> 50:26.624
* Before I do
* Time

50:26.657 --> 50:28.693
* Will

50:28.726 --> 50:29.694
* Move

50:29.727 --> 50:31.196
* On

50:31.229 --> 50:36.801
* Before I do

50:36.834 --> 50:37.835
[sighs]

50:37.868 --> 50:39.270
Okay?

50:39.304 --> 50:40.671
You didn't taste it.

50:44.809 --> 50:46.477
Needs way more salt.

50:46.511 --> 50:47.578
All right.

50:48.746 --> 50:50.181
SUNNY: Hello.

50:50.215 --> 50:51.682
Hey, we're
in the kitchen!

50:54.819 --> 50:56.087
Hey.

50:56.121 --> 50:57.088
Hi.

50:57.122 --> 50:58.356
What are you cooking?

50:58.389 --> 51:00.258
Slaw for tomorrow.

51:00.291 --> 51:02.260
Tomorrow?

51:02.293 --> 51:03.628
The picnic.

51:03.661 --> 51:06.497
Oh, yeah. I...

51:06.531 --> 51:08.333
Oh, I totally forgot.

51:08.366 --> 51:09.767
So how was your day?

51:09.800 --> 51:11.602
Disgusting.

51:11.636 --> 51:13.271
I don't think
I've ever heard the day

51:13.304 --> 51:14.472
quite described
like that before.

51:14.505 --> 51:15.606
[laughs]

51:15.640 --> 51:18.309
Well, I'm gonna
go watch some TV

51:18.343 --> 51:19.844
before I go to bed.

51:19.877 --> 51:21.312
I'll see you tomorrow.

51:21.346 --> 51:22.480
All right.

51:22.513 --> 51:25.183
I'll be over there
in a little bit.

51:25.216 --> 51:26.184
Oh, no.

51:26.217 --> 51:28.153
It's fine.

51:29.654 --> 51:31.589
[Chuckles]

51:31.622 --> 51:33.791
[Both laugh]

51:33.824 --> 51:36.261
So, um, you want
to sit outside?

51:36.294 --> 51:38.796
I can grab some beers.
Great.

51:38.829 --> 51:41.166
Uh, I'll be right there.
I'm gonna turn
the stove off.

51:41.199 --> 51:42.833
Okay.
All right.

51:58.216 --> 51:59.517
Oh.

51:59.550 --> 52:02.253
"These old highways,

52:02.287 --> 52:03.854
"these old back roads,

52:03.888 --> 52:05.223
"crooked as an arrow,

52:05.256 --> 52:06.657
but it's
where I came from."

52:06.691 --> 52:08.393
Uh, don't... Heh heh.
Don't read that.

52:08.426 --> 52:11.196
"Flat as far
as the eye can see."

52:11.196 --> 52:12.330
[wind chimes tinkling]

52:12.363 --> 52:14.732
I was, um,

52:14.765 --> 52:17.802
writing lyrics
to a new song.

52:17.835 --> 52:19.604
I like it.

52:19.637 --> 52:20.671
Yeah?

52:20.705 --> 52:22.607
Yeah.

52:22.640 --> 52:24.775
You should
finish it.

52:24.809 --> 52:26.544
Well, maybe I will.

52:29.880 --> 52:33.584
I should go.
I gotta take a shower.

52:37.755 --> 52:39.557
Maybe we could
go for a swim.

52:39.590 --> 52:41.226
[laughs]

52:41.259 --> 52:42.960
[Both laugh]

52:42.993 --> 52:45.663
So why haven't you
ever been married?

52:45.696 --> 52:47.532
I was a long time ago.

52:47.565 --> 52:48.533
Really?

52:48.566 --> 52:49.600
Yeah.

52:49.634 --> 52:51.469
What happened?

52:51.502 --> 52:54.439
Guess we just kind of
grew out of each other.

52:54.472 --> 52:56.541
We met when
I was playing ball,

52:56.574 --> 53:00.411
and when I got out,
she wanted out.

53:00.445 --> 53:03.481
She left you
just because
you quit football?

53:05.416 --> 53:09.520
Well, to be fair, it wasn't
the program she bought into.

53:11.422 --> 53:13.758
What was
that program?

53:13.791 --> 53:16.827
The guy who
paints postcards
and plays guitar?

53:16.861 --> 53:18.363
Yeah, that one.

53:19.830 --> 53:21.599
Do you like
this program?

53:21.632 --> 53:23.601
More than I liked that one.

53:23.634 --> 53:25.570
What was wrong
with that one?

53:30.375 --> 53:31.809
There was this one game.

53:31.842 --> 53:34.712
It was the fourth quarter,
and the game was on the line.

53:36.381 --> 53:38.849
75,000 people in the stands

53:38.883 --> 53:40.618
screaming,
yelling, fighting.

53:43.388 --> 53:46.557
I looked across
the line at the guy
I was playing against,

53:46.591 --> 53:48.659
and he had saliva
foaming at the mouth

53:48.693 --> 53:50.495
and blood
all over his uniform,

53:50.528 --> 53:52.029
and looked down
at my hands,

53:52.062 --> 53:55.300
and they're
bloody and broken.

53:56.701 --> 53:58.936
I start thinking,
"This is crazy."

53:58.969 --> 54:02.440
But my whole life had
been geared to this moment,

54:02.473 --> 54:06.311
just go down the field and
score the winning touchdown.

54:06.344 --> 54:07.745
I had this epiphany.

54:07.778 --> 54:09.614
What does it mean...

54:11.015 --> 54:14.319
a grown man trying to move
this piece of pigskin

54:14.352 --> 54:15.986
up and down
these white lines?

54:18.889 --> 54:22.327
It was over,
and I knew at that moment

54:22.360 --> 54:24.729
I was not
a football player anymore.

54:34.071 --> 54:36.341
SUNNY: Come on.
Be here. Be here.

54:36.341 --> 54:38.042
BUTCH:
What are you
looking for?

54:38.075 --> 54:39.844
Oh, yes. Still here.

54:39.877 --> 54:41.078
Tequila.
Oh, my God.

54:41.111 --> 54:42.480
I can't believe
it's still here.

54:42.513 --> 54:43.481
How... How old is it?

54:43.514 --> 54:44.849
Mmm. Really old,

54:44.882 --> 54:45.850
and it's good.

54:45.883 --> 54:46.917
[laughs]

54:46.951 --> 54:47.885
All right.

54:50.555 --> 54:51.489
Oh!

54:53.691 --> 54:55.025
Okay.

54:55.059 --> 54:57.462
Guess we're
dipping more
than our toes.

55:03.534 --> 55:04.602
Naked?

55:04.635 --> 55:05.670
Okay, I'm down.

55:12.109 --> 55:13.544
Come on!
I'm coming.

55:16.981 --> 55:18.616
[Squeals]

55:22.587 --> 55:23.921
Don't forget the tequila!

55:23.954 --> 55:25.956
Okay.
[laughs]

55:25.990 --> 55:27.592
Never leave
the bottle behind.

55:32.797 --> 55:34.432
Where...

55:34.465 --> 55:35.500
You gotta get
the tequila.

55:35.533 --> 55:36.467
I'll get it.

55:38.035 --> 55:40.405
How good does this feel?

55:40.405 --> 55:41.672
Hey, well,

55:41.706 --> 55:42.940
give me that thing.

55:42.973 --> 55:44.041
Here you go.

55:44.074 --> 55:45.576
[Chuckles]

55:47.712 --> 55:51.582
So, why haven't you
hooked up with anybody
since wifey?

55:51.616 --> 55:55.620
'Cause I haven't met anyone
since wifey. You?

55:55.653 --> 55:57.422
Mm...

55:57.455 --> 55:59.690
emotionally
unavailable.

55:59.724 --> 56:01.859
Heh. Perfect.

56:03.461 --> 56:04.729
[Sighs]

56:04.762 --> 56:07.565
So if we're gonna bare
our souls tonight,

56:07.598 --> 56:09.600
what happened
between you and Jackson?

56:09.634 --> 56:13.604
[Sighs]

56:13.638 --> 56:17.742
Well, um, one night,

56:17.775 --> 56:20.845
he was driving
after we'd been drinking,

56:20.878 --> 56:24.114
and he passed out
and hit a tree,

56:24.148 --> 56:27.485
and, um, I cracked
a vertebra.

56:27.518 --> 56:29.520
Oh.
Yeah.

56:29.554 --> 56:32.457
And found out
that at the time,

56:32.490 --> 56:34.625
I'd been pregnant.

56:34.659 --> 56:38.195
And Jackson called that
a cheap abortion.

56:38.228 --> 56:39.464
Oh, nice.

56:39.497 --> 56:40.498
Mm.

56:40.531 --> 56:42.199
And about the same time,

56:42.232 --> 56:45.803
Cotton's dad, my stepdad,

56:45.836 --> 56:47.505
dumped my mom,

56:47.538 --> 56:48.906
and, um...

56:48.939 --> 56:51.208
And I... I don't know.

56:51.241 --> 56:57.081
I just... I guess I realized
that I was gonna have a life

56:57.114 --> 57:01.486
just like my mom
if I didn't get out of here,

57:01.486 --> 57:04.889
and so I got on a bus
and went to L.A.

57:04.922 --> 57:07.592
So why did you
come back?

57:07.625 --> 57:09.727
Well...

57:09.760 --> 57:11.896
I got...

57:11.929 --> 57:14.965
I got Cotton's
last postcard.

57:14.999 --> 57:17.635
I think it was
the 17th postcard,

57:17.668 --> 57:22.039
and, um... and she said

57:22.072 --> 57:25.743
that Lois didn't have
many days left

57:25.776 --> 57:29.046
and maybe I could come home
and stay with her,

57:29.079 --> 57:31.048
and...

57:32.917 --> 57:35.620
I realized that...

57:37.755 --> 57:43.528
I needed to come back
and... and face my mom.

57:43.528 --> 57:45.563
[Crying]
Yeah.

57:48.265 --> 57:50.835
And I missed her by a day.

57:50.868 --> 57:52.837
I'm so sorry.

58:12.256 --> 58:14.124
Maybe we should go.

58:24.802 --> 58:26.571
Think she's
still asleep?

58:26.571 --> 58:27.738
I hope so.

58:32.710 --> 58:34.912
Sorry I'm so crazy.

58:36.647 --> 58:38.215
There's nothing crazy
about you.

58:41.118 --> 58:42.987
Night.

58:43.020 --> 58:44.589
Night.

58:58.368 --> 59:00.270
Sunny, don't do it.

59:03.140 --> 59:05.943
[Music playing]

59:05.976 --> 59:08.112
[Overlapping chatter]

59:16.386 --> 59:18.789
[Cheering]

59:23.227 --> 59:26.096
* When you touched
a friend of mine *

59:28.032 --> 59:30.034
* I thought
I would lose my mind... *

59:30.067 --> 59:31.368
BUTCH: Hey, how 'bout
right here, y'all?

59:31.401 --> 59:32.837
Oh, perfect.
Yeah?

59:32.870 --> 59:34.104
Whoa, whoa,
whoa, whoa.

59:34.138 --> 59:36.674
Hey, Judy, would you
watch Joe Boy?

59:36.707 --> 59:38.175
Oh, sure.
I'm gonna go play.

59:38.208 --> 59:39.309
Okay.
Okay.

59:39.343 --> 59:40.811
I'll see you later.

59:46.684 --> 59:47.652
Hey, Bubba!

59:47.685 --> 59:49.186
Hey, Sunny!

59:49.219 --> 59:51.388
How 'bout we set up
with y'all here?

59:51.421 --> 59:52.790
That's fine with me.

59:52.823 --> 59:54.925
BUTCH: Here, let me
help you with that.

59:54.959 --> 59:58.228
[Groans]

59:58.262 --> 59:59.830
Ow. My...

59:59.864 --> 01:00:01.666
Did you sell
that dollar?

01:00:01.699 --> 01:00:05.369
Oh, Bubba,
you know, some old boy
came in for a beer.

01:00:05.402 --> 01:00:08.639
I wasn't paying attention.
I give it away in change.

01:00:08.673 --> 01:00:11.942
Don't get very high marks
for my handling of money.

01:00:11.976 --> 01:00:15.079
[Chuckles]

01:00:15.112 --> 01:00:17.882
And, Merlin,
what'd you bring?

01:00:17.915 --> 01:00:19.349
Nothing.
There's always enough.

01:00:19.383 --> 01:00:21.185
Sandbagging?
Tree shading?

01:00:21.218 --> 01:00:22.352
Not even a beer?

01:00:22.386 --> 01:00:23.353
Well,
what'd you bring?

01:00:23.387 --> 01:00:24.689
Two cases.

01:00:24.722 --> 01:00:25.990
And that's not
gonna be enough.

01:00:26.023 --> 01:00:27.291
Listen,
all I know is

01:00:27.324 --> 01:00:29.159
the day's over
when the beer
runs out.

01:00:29.193 --> 01:00:30.427
Can I have one?

01:00:30.460 --> 01:00:32.863
Thank you, señor.
Thank you.

01:00:34.364 --> 01:00:35.365
Ledball.

01:00:35.399 --> 01:00:36.767
Hey, sweetheart.

01:00:36.801 --> 01:00:38.769
You gotta hear
my sister sing.

01:00:38.803 --> 01:00:39.770
Really, sweetheart?

01:00:39.804 --> 01:00:41.071
Yep.
Yeah?

01:00:41.105 --> 01:00:43.908
And you'll know
what I mean when you hear.

01:00:43.941 --> 01:00:45.309
[Chuckles]
Come on.

01:00:45.342 --> 01:00:46.376
Butch.
Yeah?

01:00:46.410 --> 01:00:48.913
Play something
so Sunny can sing.

01:00:48.946 --> 01:00:51.816
Uh, why don't
we just sit down
and eat something

01:00:51.849 --> 01:00:53.250
and relax a little bit
first, huh?

01:00:53.283 --> 01:00:54.251
You hungry, Cotton?

01:00:54.284 --> 01:00:56.086
No. I want to
hear you sing.

01:00:56.120 --> 01:00:57.421
Well, I'd like
to hear you sing.

01:00:57.454 --> 01:00:58.789
You want
to hear her sing?

01:00:58.823 --> 01:00:59.790
Yes.
Can't wait.

01:00:59.824 --> 01:01:01.358
CRICKET:
Yes, I do.

01:01:01.391 --> 01:01:03.828
I don't want
to sing right now.

01:01:03.861 --> 01:01:04.862
Will you later?

01:01:04.895 --> 01:01:05.830
Please?

01:01:07.765 --> 01:01:10.034
Maybe.

01:01:10.067 --> 01:01:12.269
Promise.

01:01:12.302 --> 01:01:13.738
We'll see.

01:01:13.771 --> 01:01:15.906
Sit down,
and get some food.

01:01:15.940 --> 01:01:18.943
Here. Eat some
of your salty slaw
you made last night.

01:01:18.976 --> 01:01:19.910
[Chuckles]

01:01:22.913 --> 01:01:24.348
Here. I got
a fork for you.

01:01:24.381 --> 01:01:27.852
* Ohh, yes

01:01:27.885 --> 01:01:30.254
* I'm not ready

01:01:30.287 --> 01:01:32.757
* I'm not ready

01:01:32.790 --> 01:01:35.259
* I'm not ready

01:01:35.292 --> 01:01:37.862
* Oh, yes

01:01:37.895 --> 01:01:39.897
* I'm not ready

01:01:39.930 --> 01:01:42.166
* I'm not ready

01:01:43.834 --> 01:01:47.237
* Oh, ready...

01:01:47.271 --> 01:01:50.107
You.
Watch it, missy.

01:01:50.140 --> 01:01:51.475
What?

01:01:51.508 --> 01:01:52.509
Don't "what" me!

01:01:52.542 --> 01:01:53.944
I know
what you're up to.

01:01:53.978 --> 01:01:55.946
And what is that?

01:01:55.980 --> 01:01:58.382
Jackson told me
how you came
to beg him for a job.

01:01:58.415 --> 01:01:59.850
And don't think
that you're

01:01:59.884 --> 01:02:01.351
gonna weasel your way
back into his life.

01:02:01.385 --> 01:02:02.352
He's with me now.

01:02:02.386 --> 01:02:04.889
Uh, I'm sorry, Tammy, but...

01:02:04.922 --> 01:02:07.357
And if I catch you
trying something,

01:02:07.391 --> 01:02:08.392
I'll kill you.

01:02:11.395 --> 01:02:13.330
Now get out of my way.
I have to piss.

01:02:21.138 --> 01:02:22.807
[Sighs]

01:02:25.075 --> 01:02:26.376
What ya doing?

01:02:26.410 --> 01:02:28.378
Nice girlfriend.

01:02:28.412 --> 01:02:30.848
Ah, she's harmless.

01:02:30.881 --> 01:02:34.318
Harmless
in a homicidal way.

01:02:34.351 --> 01:02:36.954
What you doing
with Butch?

01:02:36.987 --> 01:02:38.823
Enjoying the day.

01:02:41.491 --> 01:02:43.193
You and I,
we've got

01:02:43.227 --> 01:02:44.461
some unfinished
business.

01:02:44.494 --> 01:02:47.264
[Sighs]
Get your hands off me.

01:02:47.297 --> 01:02:49.333
Be happy
with what you got.

01:02:57.407 --> 01:03:00.845
You could have
brought at least
a twelver.

01:03:00.878 --> 01:03:02.479
Enough, Cricket.

01:03:04.148 --> 01:03:05.215
Where's Sunny?

01:03:05.249 --> 01:03:07.451
Oh, she'll be back
in a minute.

01:03:12.256 --> 01:03:13.590
What's wrong?

01:03:13.623 --> 01:03:16.426
Nothing.
Are we leaving?

01:03:16.460 --> 01:03:17.962
I guess.

01:03:17.995 --> 01:03:20.530
Well, aren't you guys
gonna play a song now?

01:03:20.564 --> 01:03:21.866
I think we're leaving.

01:03:23.133 --> 01:03:24.268
No.

01:03:24.301 --> 01:03:26.036
No, no, no, no, no. Now.

01:03:26.070 --> 01:03:28.172
Now is the time.
Now is the time.

01:03:28.205 --> 01:03:30.474
Come on. Come on here,
because Sunny's gonna sing!

01:03:30.507 --> 01:03:32.476
Why are you
acting like this?

01:03:32.509 --> 01:03:34.144
Because of my dream.

01:03:34.178 --> 01:03:36.013
I saw you guys
playing last night,

01:03:36.046 --> 01:03:37.514
and you have
to play now!

01:03:37.547 --> 01:03:41.151
I... I really don't
feel like singing.

01:03:41.185 --> 01:03:44.454
Maybe another time,
okay?

01:03:44.488 --> 01:03:46.156
You can't go now.

01:03:46.190 --> 01:03:48.993
Aw, sweet pea,
it's getting late.

01:03:49.026 --> 01:03:51.395
But you haven't
heard them sing,

01:03:51.428 --> 01:03:53.230
and there's
gonna be fireworks.

01:03:53.263 --> 01:03:54.965
Beer's all gone,
little sister.

01:03:54.999 --> 01:03:56.433
That means
the party's over.

01:03:56.466 --> 01:03:58.602
You could at least
bring a sixer.

01:03:58.635 --> 01:04:00.470
Cricket, you might
have a problem.

01:04:00.504 --> 01:04:02.506
Yeah, you drank
all my beer.

01:04:02.539 --> 01:04:05.910
Hey, maybe we do it
another time, all right?

01:04:05.910 --> 01:04:09.914
Why is it so important
that we play right now?

01:04:09.914 --> 01:04:12.082
It just is.

01:04:13.583 --> 01:04:16.120
You'll see.

01:04:16.153 --> 01:04:18.088
I don't know.

01:04:18.122 --> 01:04:20.090
But I know.

01:04:20.124 --> 01:04:22.459
Come on, you can
just sing that song

01:04:22.492 --> 01:04:24.528
that you were singing
in the shower.

01:04:24.561 --> 01:04:26.430
They'll love it.

01:04:28.698 --> 01:04:30.367
Whatever you
want to do.

01:04:32.536 --> 01:04:34.038
Okay.

01:04:34.071 --> 01:04:35.305
Okay?

01:04:35.339 --> 01:04:36.573
Do you know, uh,

01:04:36.606 --> 01:04:38.976
"What I Left
Back Home"?

01:04:40.510 --> 01:04:42.579
Yeah, I think I do.

01:04:44.081 --> 01:04:45.182
Okay.
Okay.

01:04:45.215 --> 01:04:46.683
I'm doing this
for you.

01:04:46.716 --> 01:04:47.684
I know.

01:04:47.717 --> 01:04:49.553
Hey, guys.
Yeah?

01:04:49.586 --> 01:04:52.289
Want to hear
one song and watch
the fireworks?

01:04:52.322 --> 01:04:54.391
Who's singing,
you or her?

01:04:54.424 --> 01:04:55.559
BUTCH:
She is.

01:04:55.592 --> 01:04:58.195
Holding out on us.
How 'bout that?

01:04:58.228 --> 01:04:59.196
Here we go.

01:04:59.229 --> 01:05:00.464
Come on, Sunny.

01:05:06.736 --> 01:05:12.142
* Millions of stars
can make you feel small *

01:05:12.176 --> 01:05:19.549
* Like a missing person's
face on a wall *

01:05:19.583 --> 01:05:23.153
* On the boulevard
of broken hearts *

01:05:23.187 --> 01:05:26.190
* There's a crowd
to watch you fall *

01:05:26.223 --> 01:05:32.997
* And you ask yourself
was it worth it all? *

01:05:33.030 --> 01:05:37.734
* All I know
is that I'm missing *

01:05:37.767 --> 01:05:41.205
* What I left at home

01:05:41.238 --> 01:05:46.043
* Guess I had to learn
on my own *

01:05:46.076 --> 01:05:52.349
* And I had
a few good reasons to go *

01:05:52.382 --> 01:05:57.321
* But I guess I had to leave
so I could know *

01:05:57.354 --> 01:06:00.557
* What I left back home

01:06:00.590 --> 01:06:03.727
* What I was
running from then *

01:06:03.760 --> 01:06:06.496
* My faults and my sins

01:06:06.530 --> 01:06:12.302
* Still followed
right behind me *

01:06:12.336 --> 01:06:17.074
* And all I know
is that I'm missing *

01:06:17.107 --> 01:06:20.377
* What I left at home

01:06:20.410 --> 01:06:25.315
* Guess I had to learn
on my own *

01:06:25.349 --> 01:06:31.655
* And I had
a few good reasons to go *

01:06:31.688 --> 01:06:36.526
* But I guess I had to leave
so I could know *

01:06:36.560 --> 01:06:44.701
* What I left back home

01:06:44.734 --> 01:06:51.175
* Home

01:06:53.343 --> 01:06:57.747
* What I left back home

01:06:57.781 --> 01:07:00.117
[cheering]
Yeah!

01:07:00.150 --> 01:07:02.286
Yes, ma'am!

01:07:02.319 --> 01:07:04.354
[Fireworks whistling]

01:07:10.594 --> 01:07:12.296
Butch, listen.

01:07:12.329 --> 01:07:14.831
You two, my place,
two weeks from Friday.

01:07:14.864 --> 01:07:16.200
It could be good.

01:07:16.233 --> 01:07:17.334
Really?

01:07:17.367 --> 01:07:18.502
We split the door,

01:07:18.535 --> 01:07:20.504
and I guarantee you
you will make more

01:07:20.537 --> 01:07:22.606
than you can at selling
watercolor postcards.

01:07:22.639 --> 01:07:24.108
[Chuckles]

01:07:24.108 --> 01:07:26.276
Nobody is gonna come
and see us play.

01:07:26.310 --> 01:07:28.612
Nobody? Nobody gonna
come see you play?

01:07:28.645 --> 01:07:31.515
Anybody want
to hear her sing?

01:07:31.548 --> 01:07:32.816
[Cheering]
Yeah!

01:07:32.849 --> 01:07:35.385
Yes, sir! Yes, sir!

01:07:35.419 --> 01:07:38.355
You want to hear more?

01:07:38.388 --> 01:07:40.224
[Cheering]
Yeah!

01:07:40.257 --> 01:07:44.494
Jack-O-Lopes!
Two weeks from Friday, 8:00!

01:07:44.528 --> 01:07:46.696
[Cheering]

01:07:51.535 --> 01:07:52.669
Let's go home,
honey.

01:07:52.702 --> 01:07:54.704
It's getting late.

01:07:54.738 --> 01:07:57.174
What you talking 'bout?

01:08:01.278 --> 01:08:04.748
What the hell are we
doing up here, anyway?

01:08:04.781 --> 01:08:06.716
[Tammy sighs]

01:08:10.254 --> 01:08:12.489
Nothing.

01:08:12.522 --> 01:08:14.258
Doing nothing.

01:08:35.645 --> 01:08:37.481
Ah, she's asleep.

01:08:37.514 --> 01:08:38.747
Okay.
[chuckles]

01:08:38.782 --> 01:08:41.618
Um, I'm just gonna...

01:08:41.651 --> 01:08:43.752
have some wine.
You want some?

01:08:43.787 --> 01:08:45.189
Yeah, sure.

01:08:47.624 --> 01:08:48.892
Hold this for me.

01:08:48.925 --> 01:08:50.627
I gotta get the glasses.

01:08:50.660 --> 01:08:52.196
They're behind you.

01:08:52.196 --> 01:08:53.197
Sorry.

01:08:54.264 --> 01:08:56.933
You know,

01:08:56.966 --> 01:09:00.270
you were amazing today,

01:09:00.304 --> 01:09:01.505
unbelievable.

01:09:05.209 --> 01:09:07.644
I've never
been unbelievable
at anything.

01:09:07.676 --> 01:09:10.346
Well, trust me,

01:09:10.380 --> 01:09:12.381
you were.

01:09:17.886 --> 01:09:19.555
Thank you.

01:09:19.589 --> 01:09:20.557
[Glasses clink]

01:09:20.590 --> 01:09:22.591
No, thank you.

01:09:22.626 --> 01:09:23.792
For everything.

01:09:28.865 --> 01:09:30.300
Um...

01:09:32.569 --> 01:09:34.404
you know,
this, um...

01:09:35.939 --> 01:09:39.376
this singing thing,

01:09:39.408 --> 01:09:40.644
you know,
these things,

01:09:40.676 --> 01:09:42.879
they just don't
work out for me.

01:09:42.912 --> 01:09:44.514
Well, maybe this will.

01:09:44.548 --> 01:09:48.252
You know, Ledball
will probably
lose his bar.

01:09:48.252 --> 01:09:51.455
Well, if we do nothing,
he will lose his bar.

01:09:57.627 --> 01:10:00.430
You're so confident.

01:10:26.623 --> 01:10:27.824
[Music playing]

01:11:01.825 --> 01:11:04.528
* There's a rock
in a field *

01:11:04.561 --> 01:11:06.430
* And a dirty sky

01:11:06.463 --> 01:11:08.665
* I'm still as a corpse

01:11:08.698 --> 01:11:11.368
* I'm content as a bride

01:11:11.401 --> 01:11:15.004
* Thoughts of you
in those flying shoes *

01:11:15.038 --> 01:11:17.674
* All around me

01:11:20.043 --> 01:11:23.980
* One wrong step,
and it's a long way down *

01:11:24.013 --> 01:11:26.816
* So I triple-check
the handholds *

01:11:26.850 --> 01:11:29.085
* And stand
on firmer ground *

01:11:29.118 --> 01:11:30.987
* But it's not so easy

01:11:31.020 --> 01:11:34.924
* When the whole mountain's
coming down on you *

01:11:37.794 --> 01:11:39.663
* So we wait
for the morning *

01:11:39.696 --> 01:11:42.466
* When we stumble
on the truth *

01:11:42.499 --> 01:11:44.634
* We fail to recognize it

01:11:44.668 --> 01:11:47.371
* As we're digging
at its roots *

01:11:47.404 --> 01:11:49.439
* The sorrow and the anger

01:11:49.473 --> 01:11:52.809
* That we've sown
in the fields all around us *

01:11:54.811 --> 01:11:56.045
There.

01:11:56.079 --> 01:11:58.448
Rip her bumper off
if you want.

01:11:58.482 --> 01:11:59.949
Let's see how this goes.

01:12:02.519 --> 01:12:04.954
[Radio playing music]

01:12:04.988 --> 01:12:07.391
Well, hello, there,
big boy.

01:12:07.424 --> 01:12:08.792
How can I do you today?

01:12:08.825 --> 01:12:10.660
I'd like to see
Jackie Williams, please.

01:12:10.694 --> 01:12:12.562
He is out of town.

01:12:12.596 --> 01:12:13.730
What else
can I do you for?

01:12:13.763 --> 01:12:15.432
How 'bout Mrs. Williams?

01:12:15.465 --> 01:12:16.800
Do you have
an appointment?

01:12:16.833 --> 01:12:18.101
Just tell her

01:12:18.134 --> 01:12:20.136
her ex-husband's
here to see her.

01:12:20.169 --> 01:12:21.405
Really?
Mm-hmm.

01:12:23.607 --> 01:12:25.542
[Chuckles]

01:12:28.512 --> 01:12:29.913
Where are your shoes?

01:12:29.946 --> 01:12:31.448
You know
I don't like 'em.

01:12:31.481 --> 01:12:32.616
Jackie treating you
okay?

01:12:32.649 --> 01:12:34.017
Mm.

01:12:34.050 --> 01:12:35.051
Bought me these.

01:12:36.420 --> 01:12:37.921
Why are you here?

01:12:37.954 --> 01:12:39.656
I need a favor.

01:12:39.689 --> 01:12:41.725
Becky Mae, do me a favor,

01:12:41.758 --> 01:12:43.126
and make me some coffee,
sweetheart.

01:12:43.159 --> 01:12:44.127
Of course.
Thank you.

01:12:46.496 --> 01:12:47.997
Well,
this should be good.

01:12:48.031 --> 01:12:50.066
I want you to broadcast
from Jack-O-Lopes.

01:12:50.099 --> 01:12:52.536
Why would
we want to do that?

01:12:52.569 --> 01:12:54.538
'Cause I'm playing with
a talented young girl
named Sunny Thompson.

01:12:54.571 --> 01:12:55.972
[Sighs]
You can't sing.

01:12:56.005 --> 01:12:58.041
Well, I'm not.
You can barely play!

01:12:58.074 --> 01:12:59.609
Well,
I've gotten better.

01:12:59.643 --> 01:13:02.446
I've never even heard
of this Sunny Thompson.

01:13:02.446 --> 01:13:04.147
Well, you will,
and you'll want
to know her.

01:13:04.180 --> 01:13:05.449
And why is that?

